org.apache.spark.sql.api.java

Class StructField

  • Object
    • org.apache.spark.sql.api.java.StructField

  • public class StructField
extends Object
    A StructField object represents a field in a StructType object. A StructField object comprises three fields, String name, DataType dataType, and boolean nullable. The field of name is the name of a StructField. The field of dataType specifies the data type of a StructField. The field of nullable specifies if values of a StructField can contain null values. The field of metadata provides extra information of the StructField. To create a StructField, DataType.createStructField(String, DataType, boolean, Metadata) should be used.
